[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Priority Ordering:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The two HIGH findings (R-1: regulatory landscape, R-2: fairness implementation) are both legitimate gaps that could result in real-world harm or compliance exposure. They don't rise to CRITICAL because the recipe does discuss the concepts (just doesn't implement them architecturally). A-1 (counterfactual tracking) is HIGH because it's a known failure mode that will definitely occur if not addressed.
