[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recipe is technically sound, well-written, and covers the core ML concerns (class imbalance, explainability, feature engineering) thoroughly. The supervised classification framing is correct and explicitly justified. The three HIGH findings are all about implementation completeness rather than fundamental incorrectness: the recipe acknowledges these concerns in prose but doesn't wire them into the architecture. Fixing these requires adding ~3-4 paragraphs of architectural guidance and updating the monitoring/feedback sections. The regulatory finding (R-1) requires adding awareness of a fast-moving legislative landscape that directly affects the use case.
